# Clarity — AI Email Assistant

> An intelligent email triage agent that reads your Gmail, categorizes messages, and drafts professional replies — powered by Claude AI.

---

## Overview

Clarity is a React-based AI agent that connects to your Gmail inbox and automatically:

- Fetches your most recent unread emails
- Categorizes each one (Urgent, Action Needed, FYI, Newsletter, Spam)
- Generates a one-sentence AI summary per email
- Drafts professional replies on demand

Built with the Anthropic Claude API and Gmail via MCP (Model Context Protocol).

---

## Tech Stack

- **Frontend** — React (JSX), inline CSS
- **AI** — Claude claude-sonnet-4-20250514 via Anthropic API
- **Email** — Gmail MCP server (`https://gmail.mcp.claude.com/mcp`)
- **Fonts** — Lora, DM Sans (Google Fonts)

---

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js 16+
- A Claude.ai account with Gmail connected under **Settings → Connections**
- An Anthropic API key

### Installation

```bash
# 1. Create a new React app
npx create-react-app clarity
cd clarity

# 2. Replace src/App.js with App.jsx from this repo
cp App.jsx src/App.js

# 3. Start the development server
npm start
```

The app will open at `http://localhost:3000`.

---

## Gmail Connection

Clarity uses Gmail via Claude's MCP integration. To enable it:

1. Go to [claude.ai](https://claude.ai) → **Settings → Connections**
2. Connect your Gmail account
3. Return to the app and click **Sort my inbox**

> Note: The Gmail MCP connection is scoped to your Claude.ai session. No credentials are stored in the app.

---

## How It Works

```
User clicks "Sort my inbox"
        ↓
Claude calls Gmail MCP → fetches 10 unread emails
        ↓
Claude categorizes + summarizes each email
        ↓
User selects an email → clicks "Generate reply"
        ↓
Claude drafts a professional reply
        ↓
User edits and copies the reply
```

---

## Email Categories

| Category | Description |
|---|---|
| 🔴 Urgent | Time-sensitive, needs immediate attention |
| 🟠 Action Needed | Requires a response or follow-up |
| 🔵 FYI | Informational, no reply needed |
| 💜 Newsletter | Subscriptions and marketing |
| ⚫ Spam | Junk or irrelevant email |

